						<summary>

						<p>Hero-stone near the Chandravaṅka river.</p>						

						<p>Birudu Kāmaya: 1066 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 988</hi> corresponding to 1066 A.D.</p>						

						<p>It states that a certain individual, whose name is not clear, entered the army of Birudu Gāmaya, son of Uriya-Bētarāju and <hi rend="italic">mahādēvi</hi> Mēḍama and offered his head to Paḍlasāni (goddess) for his master. The sculpture of the hero was made by Vaṁkōjunṟu Iruga <hi rend="italic">i.e.,</hi> Iruga, son of Vaṅkōja.</p>						

						</summary>
